THREAD

China and India have agreed to disengage their troops from a months-long standoff at their long-disputed Himalayan border.

In this thread, we help you understand the border tensions between India and China - in 7 maps üëá https://t.co/Xm8lXFlmLY https://t.co/qW9GE1tBUV

name: AJEnglish
text:
India and China share the world's longest disputed border (3,500km).

These border problems are rooted in the demarcation of boundaries by British colonial rulers.

The disputes were in three different sectors: the Eastern, Central and Western https://t.co/TRpWEqI24J https://t.co/NV6heMBlhd

name: AJEnglish
text:
Arunachal Pradesh, which shares a 1,129km (700-mile) border with China, forms part of the Eastern sector.

The state, which is claimed by Beijing, was at the centre of a full-scale border war in 1962 when India lost some territory to China https://t.co/76bf3d95Xw https://t.co/0jNctF3Elf

name: AJEnglish
text:
